% Instructions
- Keep business logic in React hooks/callbacks with explicit loading/error handling for async API calls.
- Preserve local vs remote execution behavior differences; remote mode reports submission success rather than immediate command completion.
- Keep architecture graph interactions functional in both normal and edit mode, including dependency editing and position updates.
- Pass all required props through to child components exactly as expected by their contracts.
- Keep the module resilient to partial failures (show alerts/messages, keep UI usable, and always clear pending modal flags in completion paths).

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/frontend/components/ArchitectureView.tsx`
- Export: default `ArchitectureView` and named `moduleNeedsSync`
